§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We want to discuss a function which repeats itself on
    regular intervals.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will introduce this after the functions
        $\sin$, $\cos$, etc. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function $f: 𝗥 → 𝗥$ is ❬periodic with period❭ $α ∈ 𝗥$
    if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(x + α) = f(x) ⦉
    ⦉
    for all $x ∈ 𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ In this case we call $f$ ❬$α$-periodic❭. ⦉
⦉

